International trade secretary Ann-Marie Trevelyan announced the programme which is expected to lift 30 million people out of extreme poverty, create jobs and provide commercial opportunities across Africa and the UK. Minister for Africa Vicky Ford said the funding will "support a more prosperous, greener continent" and "deliver free and fairer trade systems". In the UK it will remove market access barriers, making it easier to export goods and services across the member states. FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES...  